   "source": [
    "# FiftyOne MR-RATE Tutorial\n",
    "### Visualize 200 Brain MRI Samples with Pathology Labels and Embeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "These prerequisite instructions relate to running the notebook in a clean venv with Python 3.10 and Jupyter Notebook. Depending on your environment, you may need to make a few tweaks to these steps.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1. Create project folder and virtual environment\n",
    "```\n",
    "mkdir ~/mr-rate-project\n",
    "cd ~/mr-rate-project\n",
    "pyenv local 3.10.14\n",
    "python -m venv mr-rate-env\n",
    "source mr-rate-env/bin/activate\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2. Install all dependencies\n",
    "```\n",
    "pip install --upgrade pip\n",
    "```\n",
    "```\n",
    "pip install \"numpy==1.26.4\" \"pymongo==4.6.3\" \"fiftyone\" \"nibabel==5.2.1\" \"pandas==2.2.2\" \"pillow==10.3.0\" \"huggingface_hub\" \"torch\" \"torchvision\" \"scikit-learn==1.3.2\" \"starlette==0.27.0\" \"strawberry-graphql==0.220.0\" \"notebook\" \"ipykernel\"\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3. Register the virtual environment as a Jupyter kernel\n",
    "```\n",
    "python -m ipykernel install --user --name=mr-rate-env --display-name=\"Python (mr-rate-env)\"\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4. Copy this notebook into the project folder\n",
    "Move this `.ipynb` file to `~/mr-rate-project/`\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5. Launch Jupyter from the project folder\n",
    "```\n",
    "cd ~/mr-rate-project\n",
    "source mr-rate-env/bin/activate\n",
    "jupyter notebook\n",
    "```\n",
    "A browser tab will open automatically.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Notes\n",
    "- FiftyOne does **NOT** display inside this notebook. When you reach Step 12, open your browser at **http://localhost:5151**\n",
    "- Similarity search in the FiftyOne UI requires a FifytOne Enterprise subscription. Use the terminal-based similarity search in Step 15 instead\n",
    "- If you see OpenMP warnings, ignore them — they are harmless\n",
    "- Every time you return, run: `cd ~/mr-rate-project && source mr-rate-env/bin/activate && jupyter notebook`\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
