   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "login(token=\"hf_your_token_here\")  # replace with your actual token\n",
    "print('Logged in to HuggingFace')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-004",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 3 — Download CSVs\n",
    "Downloads metadata, radiology reports, and pathology labels. Fast — just text files."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-03",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "local_dir = os.path.expanduser(\"~/mr-rate-project/mr-rate\")\n",
    "os.makedirs(local_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "for filename in [\n",
    "    \"metadata/batch00_metadata.csv\",\n",
    "    \"reports/batch00_reports.csv\",\n",
    "    \"pathology_labels/mrrate_labels.csv\",\n",
    "]:\n",
    "    hf_hub_download(\n",
    "        repo_id=\"Forithmus/MR-RATE\",\n",
    "        repo_type=\"dataset\",\n",
    "        filename=filename,\n",
    "        local_dir=local_dir,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\"Downloaded {filename}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSaved to {local_dir}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-005",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 4 — Download 20 study zips\n",
    "\n",
    "Each zip is one MRI study (~8–15 series). 20 zips gives ~150–200 NIfTI files.\n",
    "\n",
    "⏱ **This will take a few minutes depending on your internet speed.**\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: The zips are at `mri/batch00/` in the repo — not `native_brain/` as some docs suggest."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-04",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "all_files = list(list_repo_files(repo_id=\"Forithmus/MR-RATE\", repo_type=\"dataset\"))\n",
    "zips = sorted([f for f in all_files if f.endswith(\".zip\") and \"batch00\" in f])\n",
    "print(f\"Found {len(zips)} zips in batch00\")\n",
    "print(f\"Downloading first 20...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, z in enumerate(zips[:20]):\n",
    "    hf_hub_download(\n",
    "        repo_id=\"Forithmus/MR-RATE\",\n",
    "        repo_type=\"dataset\",\n",
    "        filename=z,\n",
    "        local_dir=local_dir,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\"  [{i+1}/20] {z}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nAll zips downloaded\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-006",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 5 — Unzip study folders"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "extract_dir = os.path.join(local_dir, \"extracted\")\n",
    "os.makedirs(extract_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "count = 0\n",
    "for root, _, files in os.walk(local_dir):\n",
    "    for fname in sorted(files):\n",
    "        if fname.endswith(\".zip\"):\n",
    "            zip_path = os.path.join(root, fname)\n",
    "            with zipfile.ZipFile(zip_path, \"r\") as z:\n",
    "                z.extractall(extract_dir)\n",
    "            count += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Unzipped {count} study folders\")\n",
    "print(f\"Extracted to: {extract_dir}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-007",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 6 — Load and merge CSVs\n",
    "\n",
    "Joins metadata + radiology reports + pathology labels all on `study_uid`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: The metadata `series_id` column contains only the sequence name (e.g. `flair-raw-sag`) without the study prefix. The filenames contain both (e.g. `25OMBCSHXB_flair-raw-sag`). We split on `_` to match them correctly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-06",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_meta    = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(local_dir, \"metadata/batch00_metadata.csv\"), low_memory=False)\n",
    "df_reports = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(local_dir, \"reports/batch00_reports.csv\"))\n",
    "df_labels  = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(local_dir, \"pathology_labels/mrrate_labels.csv\"))\n",
    "label_cols = [c for c in df_labels.columns if c != \"study_uid\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.merge(df_meta, df_reports, on=\"study_uid\", how=\"left\")\n",
    "df = pd.merge(df, df_labels,  on=\"study_uid\", how=\"left\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Metadata rows:   {len(df_meta)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Reports rows:    {len(df_reports)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Labels rows:     {len(df_labels)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Merged shape:    {df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Pathologies:     {len(label_cols)} conditions\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-008",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 7 — Find NIfTI files\n",
    "Skips segmentation masks in the `/seg/` subfolder. Limits to 200 files."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-07",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nifti_files = []\n",
    "for root, _, files in os.walk(extract_dir):\n",
    "    for f in sorted(files):\n",
    "        path = os.path.join(root, f)\n",
    "        if f.endswith(\".nii.gz\") and \"/seg/\" not in path:\n",
    "            nifti_files.append(path)\n",
    "        if len(nifti_files) >= 200:\n",
    "            break\n",
    "    if len(nifti_files) >= 200:\n",
    "        break\n",
    "\n",
    "nifti_files = nifti_files[:200]\n",
    "print(f\"Found {len(nifti_files)} NIfTI files\")\n",
    "print(f\"Example: {nifti_files[0]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-009",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 8 — Convert NIfTI volumes to PNG slices\n",
    "\n",
    "Each 3D MRI volume is a stack of 2D slices. We extract the middle axial slice and save it as a PNG so FiftyOne can display it.\n",
    "\n",
    "⏱ First run takes ~1–2 minutes. Re-runs skip already-converted files instantly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "png_dir = os.path.join(local_dir, \"slices\")\n",
    "os.makedirs(png_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "def nifti_to_png(nifti_path, out_path):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Extract middle axial slice from a NIfTI volume and save as PNG.\"\"\"\n",
    "    vol = nib.load(nifti_path).get_fdata()\n",
    "    if vol.ndim == 4:\n",
    "        vol = vol[..., 0]        # first timepoint if 4D\n",
    "    mid = vol.shape[2] // 2      # middle axial slice\n",
    "    slc = vol[:, :, mid]\n",
    "    slc = slc - slc.min()\n",
    "    if slc.max() > 0:\n",
    "        slc = slc / slc.max()\n",
    "    slc = (slc * 255).astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "    Image.fromarray(slc).save(out_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "converted = 0\n",
    "skipped   = 0\n",
    "for i, nifti_path in enumerate(nifti_files):\n",
    "    base     = os.path.basename(nifti_path)[:-7]\n",
    "    png_path = os.path.join(png_dir, base + \".png\")\n",
    "    if not os.path.exists(png_path):\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            nifti_to_png(nifti_path, png_path)\n",
    "            converted += 1\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"  Skipping {base}: {e}\")\n",
    "            skipped += 1\n",
    "    if (i + 1) % 50 == 0:\n",
    "        print(f\"  Processed {i + 1}/{len(nifti_files)}...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nConverted: {converted} new PNGs\")\n",
    "print(f\"Skipped:   {skipped} errors\")\n",
    "print(f\"Saved to:  {png_dir}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-010",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 9 — Build FiftyOne samples\n",
    "\n",
    "For each NIfTI file:\n",
    "- Links to its PNG slice\n",
    "- Splits filename into `study_uid` + `series_id` to match metadata correctly\n",
    "- Attaches acquisition metadata (modality, sequence, age, sex, manufacturer)\n",
    "- Attaches radiology report fields (findings, impression, technique)\n",
    "- Attaches pathology labels as FiftyOne Classifications\n",
    "- Adds `primary_pathology` as a single string field for easy filtering and coloring in the embeddings panel"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "samples = []\n",
    "skipped = 0\n",
    "matched = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, nifti_path in enumerate(nifti_files):\n",
    "    # Filename: 25OMBCSHXB_flair-raw-sag.nii.gz\n",
    "    # study_uid = 25OMBCSHXB  (matches metadata study_uid column)\n",
    "    # series_id = flair-raw-sag  (matches metadata series_id column)\n",
    "    base      = os.path.basename(nifti_path)[:-7]\n",
    "    parts     = base.split(\"_\", 1)\n",
    "    study_uid = parts[0]\n",
    "    series_id = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    png_path = os.path.join(png_dir, base + \".png\")\n",
    "    if not os.path.exists(png_path):\n",
    "        skipped += 1\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "\n",
    "    sample = fo.Sample(filepath=png_path)\n",
    "    sample[\"nifti_path\"] = nifti_path\n",
    "    sample[\"series_id\"]  = series_id\n",
    "    sample[\"study_uid\"]  = study_uid\n",
    "\n",
    "    row = df[(df[\"study_uid\"] == study_uid) & (df[\"series_id\"] == series_id)]\n",
    "    if not row.empty:\n",
    "        matched += 1\n",
    "        r = row.iloc[0]\n",
    "        # Acquisition metadata\n",
    "        for field in [\"classified_modality\", \"sequence_family\", \"acquisition_plane\",\n",
    "                      \"array_shape\", \"array_spacing_mm\", \"Patient'sAge\",\n",
    "                      \"Patient'sSex\", \"Manufacturer\"]:\n",
    "            if field in r and pd.notna(r[field]):\n",
    "                sample[field.replace(\"'\", \"\").replace(\" \", \"_\")] = str(r[field])\n",
    "        # Radiology report\n",
    "        for field in [\"findings\", \"impression\", \"technique\", \"clinical_information\"]:\n",
    "            if field in r and pd.notna(r[field]):\n",
    "                sample[field] = str(r[field])\n",
    "        # Pathology labels as Classifications (multi-label)\n",
    "        positive = [l for l in label_cols if pd.notna(r.get(l)) and r[l] == 1]\n",
    "        sample[\"pathologies\"] = fo.Classifications(\n",
    "            classifications=[fo.Classification(label=l) for l in positive]\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        sample[\"normal\"] = len(positive) == 0\n",
    "        # Primary pathology as single string for easy coloring in embeddings panel\n",
    "        sample[\"primary_pathology\"] = positive[0] if positive else \"Normal\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    samples.append(sample)\n",
    "    if (i + 1) % 50 == 0:\n",
    "        print(f\"  Processed {i + 1}/{len(nifti_files)}...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDone — {len(samples)} samples, {matched} matched, {skipped} skipped\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-011",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 10 — Load into FiftyOne and save"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dataset = fo.Dataset(\"MR-RATE-200\", overwrite=True)\n",
    "dataset.add_samples(samples)\n",
    "dataset.persistent = True   # saves the dataset so it survives restarts\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(dataset)} samples\")\n",
    "print(f\"Fields: {list(dataset.get_field_schema().keys())}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-012",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 11 — Check pathology distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-11",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "\n",
    "counts = Counter()\n",
    "normal_count = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "for sample in dataset:\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        if sample[\"pathologies\"]:\n",
    "            for c in sample[\"pathologies\"].classifications:\n",
    "                counts[c.label] += 1\n",
    "        if sample[\"normal\"]:\n",
    "            normal_count += 1\n",
    "    except:\n",
    "        pass\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total samples:         {len(dataset)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Normal (no pathology): {normal_count}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nPathology distribution:\")\n",
    "for label, count in counts.most_common():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {label}: {count}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-013",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 12 — Launch FiftyOne\n",
    "\n",
    "⚠️ **FiftyOne does NOT display inside this notebook.**\n",
    "\n",
    "After running this cell open a new browser tab and go to **http://localhost:5151**\n",
    "\n",
    "### What to explore in the UI\n",
    "| Feature | How |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| Filter by pathology | Left sidebar → click `pathologies` → select a condition |\n",
    "| Filter normal vs abnormal | Left sidebar → click `normal` → True or False |\n",
    "| Filter by modality | Left sidebar → click `classified_modality` → select T1/T2/FLAIR/SWI |\n",
    "| Read radiology report | Click any image → scroll to `findings` or `impression` |\n",
    "| Open embeddings panel | Click **Embeddings** tab at top of screen |\n",
    "| Color embeddings | In Embeddings panel → **Color by** dropdown → scroll down to `primary_pathology` |"
